@flag
@FLAG

Set or unset flags on an object

Syntax: @flag <object dbref/name>=<flagstring>

A flag string consists of a series of letters and numbers. To remove a single flag, simply
put an '!' character in front of a single character that represents the flag to be removed.
Multiple flags may be added, but only one flag can be removed at a time.

